    <glossary>
    <definition id="def-00001"><term>Jensen’s alpha</term> <meaning>a measure of portfolio performance, calculated as the raw portfolio return minus the expected portfolio return predicted by the CAPM</meaning></definition>
    <definition id="def-00002"><term>Sharpe ratio</term> <meaning>a reward-to-risk measure of portfolio performance, calculated by subtracting the risk-free rate from the average portfolio return and then dividing by the standard deviation of the portfolio</meaning></definition>
    <definition id="def-00003"><term>Treynor ratio</term> <meaning>a reward-to-risk measure of portfolio performance, calculated by subtracting the risk-free rate from the average portfolio return and then dividing by the beta of the portfolio</meaning></definition>
    </glossary>    
